    "The result of effective population size (Ne; Additional file 2: Fig.",
    "S5) exhibited similar divergent time.",
    "We therefore speculate that Tartary buckwheat spread to Europe with the expansion of the Mongol Empire, which was also illustrated in 'The History of The Mongol Empire'.To evaluate the accuracy of the candidate dispersal route of Tartary buckwheat, we divided Tartary buckwheat accessions into ten mini-groups based on geographical distribution.",
    "The silhouette score based on genotype showed the groups can be well clustered (Additional file 2: Fig.",
    "The f 3 statistics revealed the genetic relationship between HW and SL is comparable to that between HW and NL, suggesting HW is the common ancestor of SL and NL groups (Fig. 2c)."
